text: Kenneth Joseph Marino (born December 19, 1968) is an American actor, comedian, director, and screenwriter. He was a cast member on MTV's The State and has starred in shows such as Party Down, Marry Me, Burning Love, and Childrens Hospital. ==References== Category:1968 births Category:Living people Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:American voice actors Category:American stage actors Category:American television writers Category:American television directors Category:American television producers Category:Comedians from New York City Category:Screenwriters from New York City Category:Actors from New York City
